  <Markdown id="intro">
## Digit Span Memory Task

Test your working memory by listening to number sequences and typing them back.
  </Markdown>

  <!-- Forward span -->
  <Markdown id="forward_instructions">
### Forward Digit Span

Listen to the sequence, then type the numbers **in the same order** you heard them.
  </Markdown>
  <DigitSpanTask id="forward_test" mode="forward" />

  <Markdown id="backward_instructions">
### Backward Digit Span

Listen to the sequence, then type the numbers **in reverse order**.
  </Markdown>
  <DigitSpanTask id="backward_test" mode="backward" />

  <Markdown id="ascending_instructions">
### Ascending Digit Span

Listen to the sequence, then type the numbers **from smallest to largest**.
  </Markdown>
  <DigitSpanTask id="ascending_test" mode="ascending" />

  <Markdown id="explanation">
### About This Task

The digit span task is a classic measure of working memory capacity. The sequence length adapts based on your performance - correct answers lead to longer sequences, while errors lead to shorter ones.

This adaptive approach provides a more accurate estimate of your memory span than fixed-length tests.
  </Markdown>

